It took a doctor telling Australian model Annaliese Gann that she needed to gain weight or risk her organs failing to turn her life around. "I was at the most unhealthy moment in my life. I went to see a doctor, and she told me if I didn't put on weight now, my internal system may start failing," the 22-year-old recently revealed on Instagram. "I was miserable â€” always cold, lifeless, and struggled to get through the day. I survived on salads and black coffee... I was at the unhealthiest moment in my life." After the doctor's visit, the now proudly curvy model began her journey to recovery. And this started by embracing her bigger frame "for what it is". My #transformationstory continued.... thinner doesn't always mean happier! The girl on the left (me pictured in Sweden size 6) was miserable, always cold, lifeless and struggled to get through the day. I survived on salads and black coffee. This girl didn't understand balance. I was at my unhealthiest moment in my life. I went to see a doctor and she told me if I didn't put on weight now my internal system may start failing. That moment turned my life around forever and I begun my journey to recovery. Pictured right (me now size 14) I'm the healthiest I've ever been. I am not also truly happy! â˜ºï¸ I work out because I love my body, not hate it. I embrace my bigger frame for what it is. I now understand BALANCE and I'm happier being my self. A reminder that YOUR natural state is different to everyone else's so try not compare yourself to others. You don't have to look like the people in the magazines to be happy, just be yourself and embrace this beautiful life. (Thank you again for reading my story and showing support on my last post) ğŸ™ğŸ½â¤ï¸ A post shared by  ANNALIESE GANN ğŸ°ğŸ’• (@annaliesegann) on May 27, 2018 at 6:18am PDT   In another post, she acknowledges that she is not naturally thin, and upon accepting this, she started living life in her true self. "I am at my natural size. I am truly myself; the